radiographic_examinations.findings: Liver and gallbladder unremarkable; 1 cm cystic lesion in the uncinate process, no main ductal dilatation; fluid-filled, enlarged appendix measuring 13 mm with hyperemic mucosa and wall edema; enhancing 6 mm focus at the uterine fundus, likely an endometrial polyp; no bowel obstruction; no free fluid or pneumoperitoneum; no abscess; no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy; a few left periuterine varices; small fat containing umbilical hernia.
